“It’s just laser, right?”
Wrong. It’s not a toy—it’s a medical device that demands science, skill, and safety.

✨ Lasers may look simple, but they require in-depth knowledge of laser physics, skin biology, and patient-specific variables like skin tone, conditions, and sensitivity.

😟 It’s disheartening to see people risk burns, scars, or infections—just to save a few bucks. Untrained hands + powerful tech = dangerous outcomes.

🚩 No protective eyewear, poor hygiene, visible distress—if you’ve seen this, you’ve already seen red flags.

🏥 At a certified dermatology clinic, you’re not just paying for a session.
You’re investing in a doctor’s expertise, clinical-grade hygiene, and long-term skin safety.

So next time you think, “But my salon does it cheaper...” — remember, you can’t compare experience with shortcuts.
